-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Gafisa, Cosan, and Vale Were Active
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   L a y a
-- 2012-07-06T21:09:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/brazilian-stock-movers-gafisa-cosan-and-vale-were-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the market close. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 1.7 percent to 55,394.05.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS), the Brazilian homebuilder, fell 5.4
percent to 2.44 reais. The company received a subpoena from the
U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on June 14 requesting
all documents used for financial statements as far back as Jan.
1, 2010. The company said today it filed 2010 and 2011 annual
reports to the SEC.  Cosan SA Industria e Comercio (CSAN3)  (CSAN3 BS), a renewable
energy and infrastructure company, fell 0.2 percent to 31.20
reais after a company official said production in Brazil’s
center south region will be lower than previously estimated.  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS), fell 1.5 percent to 39.88 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer dropped as metals prices
declined after a report showing slower-than-forecast job gains
in the U.S. The Bloomberg Base Metals 3-Month Price Commodity
Index fell 2.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Laya in  New York  at 
